name: src/adapters/Adapter.js
Adapter
description:
The data adapter interface for managing data persistence asynchronously.
  Abstract class.

description: Create a new system.

name: src/adapters/VolatileAdapter.js
VolatileAdapter
description:
Manage systems in volatile memory. Nothing is persisted beyond the lifetime
  of the process.

name: constructor
description:
Create a new instance of the VolatileAdapter class. Constructs the
  internal system map.

name: createSystem
description: Create a new system and store it in the system map.

name: getSystem
description: Get an existing system from the system map.

name: updateSystem
description: Update an existing system in the system map.

name: src/errors/CustomError.js
CustomError
description:
An error class which can be extended and correctly assigns a name, message
  and stack to each instance.

name: constructor
description: Create an error instance.

params.name: message
params.description: Assigns a message to this instance

name: message
description: A brief explanation of the error that occurred.

name: stack
description: Stack trace of the error's origin.

name: name
description: Get this error's name. Will be the same as the constructor's name.

NotImplementedError

name: src/Registry.js
Identifier
description:
Identifiers can be any unique value which adapters will use to identify a
  system. The identifier is preferably JSON-serializable (i.e. a String or
  Number) however the individual adapter may accept other data types.

name: Registry
description:
A registry maintains a list of systems and their details.
It must be initialised with a data persistence adapter.

name: constructor
description: Create a new instance of the Registry class.

name: adapter
description:
Data adapter. Each registry must have an adapter which decides if and
  how data is persisted and retrieved.

description: Create a new system.
